{"lemma":"جِسْرَيْ","slug":"جِسْرَيْ","root":"ج.س.ر","root_slug":"ج-س-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-س-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5794","n5797","n5798"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bridge"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to arch, to vault (a bridge)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to span, to traverse, to cross (as if by a bridge)","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَسَرَ (jasara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dare, to risk, to venture","tags":["transitive"],"examples":[{"text":"لَا يَجْسُرُ أَنْ يَفْعَلَ كَذَا.","english":"He dares not do such a thing."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to act boldly or courageously","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Jessore (a city in Bangladesh)","tags":["transitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic גִּישְׁרָא / גִּשְׁרָא (gišrā) / ܓܫܪܐ (gešrā), with Hebrew גֶּשֶׁר (géšer) from Akkadian 𒄀𒅖𒊒 (gišru, “bridge”). Note the meaning “timber, beam” in Syriac – originally the Arabic word meant a wooden bridge in distinction from a stone bridge قَنْطَرَة (qanṭara). The word has a derivation in Akkadian from 𒄑𒃡 (GIŠ.ÙR), 𒄑𒃡𒋗 (GIŠ.ŠU.ÙR /⁠gušūru, gašūru⁠/, “tree-trunk; felled log, timber; beams”), itself considered a Sumerian loanword.\n\nDenominal verb of جِسْر (jisr, “bridge”).\n\nBorrowed from Classical Persian جَسَر (jasar), from Bengali যশোর (jośōr)."},"ipa":["/d͡ʒisr/","/d͡ʒa.sa.ra/","/d͡ʒasr/","/d͡ʒa.sar/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5794","headword_ar":"جَسَرَ","root":"jsr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasaArapN","text_ar":"جَسَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K, KL) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jusuwrN","text_ar":"جُسُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a man, (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was daring, courageous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bold:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, KL:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he acted with penetrating energy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sharpness, vigorousness, and effectiveness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaY","text_ar":"مَضَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nafa*a","text_ar":"نَفَذَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasara EalaY ka*aA","text_ar":"جَسَرَ عَلَى كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasaArapN","text_ar":"جَسَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ventured upon such a thing daringly, courageously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boldly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tjAsr","text_ar":"تجاسر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tjAsr","text_ar":"تجاسر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he emboldened himself against it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasara EalaY Eaduw~ihi","text_ar":"جَسَرَ عَلَى عَدُوِّهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jusuwrN","text_ar":"جُسُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasaArapN","text_ar":"جَسَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acted daringly, conrageously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"boldly, against his enemy."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yajosuru A^ano yafoEala ka*aA","text_ar":"لَا يَجْسُرُ اَنْ يَفْعَلَ كَذَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dares not to do such a thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasara","text_ar":"جَسَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasorN","text_ar":"جَسْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arched,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vaulted, a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jisor","text_ar":"جِسْر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bridge"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b2-  It is said of [the giant] 'Ooj ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euwj","text_ar":"عُوج"},{"kind":"text","text":"), in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqaEa EalaY niyli miSora","text_ar":"وَقَعَ عَلَى نِيلِ مِصْرَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fajasarahumo sanapF","text_ar":"فَجَسَرَهُمْ سَنَةً"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e., (tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He fell down upon the Nile of Egypt, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became a bridge to them"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the space of a year"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b3-  And one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasarati","text_ar":"جَسَرَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~ikaAbu AlmafaAzapa","text_ar":"الرِّكَابُ المَفَازَةَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AijotasaratohaA","text_ar":"اِجْتَسَرَتْهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The travellingcamels crossed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed over, the desert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as by a bridge:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~afiynapu AlbaHora","text_ar":"السَّفِينَةُ البَحْرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajtsrti","text_ar":"اجتسرتِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The ship crossed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed over, the sea:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rode upon, and passed through, the sea."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","A","KL","S","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n5797","headword_ar":"جَسْرٌ","root":"jsr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasuwrN","text_ar":"جَسُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b2-  Also, applied to a he-camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sharp, spirited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vigorous; syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maADK","text_ar":"مَاضٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliydN","text_ar":"بَلِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasorapN","text_ar":"جَسْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mutajaAsirapN","text_ar":"مُتَجَاسِرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a she-camel: or (so in the K accord. to the TA; but in the CK, “ and ”)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall and bulky:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a she-camel, it has this last signification; (TA;) or signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strong, and bold to endure travel:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) the masc. epithet applied to a he-camel is rare. (Lth, TA.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Large,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bulky;"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a camel, (S, K,) &c., (S,) or to anything, (K,) or to any limb, or member: (TA:) fem. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasorapu Als~awaAEidi","text_ar":"جَسْرَةُ السَّوَاعِدِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuxad~ami","text_ar":"المُخَدَّمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Full"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plump"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the fore arms,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the place of the anklet"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; applied to a girl, or young woman. (A, TA.)       -A2-  See also what next follows."}],"source_refs":["K","A","TA","S"]},{"entry_id":"n5798","headword_ar":"جِسْرٌ","root":"jsr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jasorN","text_ar":"جَسْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A bridge;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dyke,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"causeway:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that on which one crosses over a river or the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanoTarap","text_ar":"قَنْطَرَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether built or not built:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a bridge of boats; boats bound together, and tied to stakes in the bank, being over a river;"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qanoTarapN","text_ar":"قَنْطَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl. (of pauc., TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ajosurN","text_ar":"اَجْسُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and (of mult., TA)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jusuwrN","text_ar":"جُسُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Msb, K.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almawotu jisorN yuwaS~ilu AlHabiyba","text_ar":"المَوْتُ جِسْرٌ يُوَصِّلُ الحَبِيبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY AlHabiybi","text_ar":"اـِلَى الحَبِيبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Death is a bridge that conveys the friend to the friend"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEala TaAEatahu","text_ar":"جَعَلَ طَاعَتَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jisorFA A_ilaY najaAtihi","text_ar":"جِسْرًا اـِلَى نَجَاتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made his obedience a bridge to his safety"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","TA","K"]}]}}